<file path=".claude/commands/ui-critique.md">
Create a `CritiqueReport` for the current task.

Arguments: $ARGUMENTS

## Evaluate at least

- hierarchy
- consistency
- novelty / non-genericity
- accessibility
- responsiveness
- implementation cleanliness

## Required output

- numeric or labeled scores
- concrete issues
- affected layer for each issue
- prioritized next actions

## Layer mapping

- hierarchy issue -> layout
- generic style issue -> tokens/style system
- state inconsistency -> components
- hardcoded values -> token / implementation
- a11y issue -> component implementation
</file>

<file path=".claude/commands/ui-layout.md">
Create or update a `LayoutSpec` for the current task.

Arguments: $ARGUMENTS

## Your job

Design the structural layout of the screen independent of final styling.

## Must include

- screen_id
- top-level regions
- role of each region
- priority order
- responsive rules
- information hierarchy
- primary action placement
- overflow behavior for smaller screens

## Rules

- preserve imported structure when working from an existing frame
- solve hierarchy before decoration
- do not hardcode visual style here
- prefer reusable layout patterns already present in the repo
</file>

<file path=".claude/commands/ui-repair.md">
Repair the current UI based on the latest CritiqueReport.

Arguments: $ARGUMENTS

## Your job

Fix only the failing layers and avoid unrelated drift.

## Rules

- identify the target layer for each issue before editing
- do not restyle the whole screen for a small implementation bug
- do not change layout when the issue is only token-related
- update stories if interaction or states changed
- preserve component reuse discipline
</file>

